@remark &&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&
@node INTRO "Introduction"
 
 Ever wanted to freq a node but didn't know the number?? Well help is here
 now!
 
 Comprehensive Nodelist searching utility. Can choose to limit the search
 to a certain subrange. Has a powerful LFORMAT (custom output) option. 
 Supports multiple wildcards. Can search on phone number, location, sysop
 name and BBS name.

@endnode
@remark &&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&
@node INSTALL "Installation"

 To install simply follow the steps below (clicking on the button will 
 automatically do the action!)
 
 1. @{"Copy FindXXX to MAIL:bin" SYSTEM "Copy FindXXX TO MAIL:bin"} 
 2. @{"Copy FindXXX.guide to MAIL:docs" SYSTEM "Copy FindXXX.guide#? TO MAIL:docs"}
@endnode
@remark &&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&
@node USAGE "Usage"

 FindXXX accepts the following argument template:

         @{i}PATTERN/M/A,S=STYPE/K,START/K,STOP/K,FULL/S,POINTS/S,
         VERBATIM/S,STRIPDASHES/S,BUFSIZE/K/N,LFORMAT/K,NODELIST/K@{ui}

 PATTERN --- Wildcard to search the nodelist for. All standard Amiga wildcards
     are supported. The search is case-insensitive. At least one pattern must
     be given but you can supply more.

 STYPE --- Type of search. You can search for node names, sysops names, phone
     numbers and location. Set to one of the follwing:
         system -- search on node name (default)
         sysop  -- search on sysop's name
         phone  -- search the phone numbers
         place  -- search the locations
     You can use S for short to specify this option.
 
 START --- Node to start the search from. For example "START=2:" would start
     the search at zone 2, skiping zone 1. If not given the search starts at
     the front of the nodelist.

 STOP --- Node to stop the search on. If not given they the nodelist is
     search to the end.

 FULL --- Specifies the output mode. If this switch is not specified then for
     each node found only 1 line of information is display. However if it
     is specified then more data is displayed.

 POINTS --- If specified then points are included in the search.

 VARBATIM --- Entries will not be subject to conversion before searching,
     in particular the phone number will not be parsed.

 BUFSIZE --- Size of the nodelist scanning buffer (in records). Values below
     32 will use the default buffer size.

 LFORMAT --- The most powerful option. This allows you to use a custom
     output format. It is similar to the LFORMAT option of List. The argument
     is a string which can contain the following formatting codes:
         %% -- %
         %n -- newline
         %t -- tab
         %r -- return
         %v -- vertical tab
         %q -- "
         %a -- BEL (alert/beep charcater)
         %b -- backspace character
         %S -- system name
         %A -- system address (short for "%z:%e/%N.%p")
         %l -- system location
         %s -- sysop's name
         %T -- type of system
         %P -- phone number
         %B -- baudrate
         %c -- accounting information
         %f -- nodelist flags
         %w -- password
         %z -- zone number
         %e -- net number
         %N -- node number
         %p -- point number
         %R -- region
         %h -- hub
     If this option is not given then 
         "%A %S, %l, %s, %P"
     is used unless the FULL option is specified, then
         "Node %A, %q%S%q is in %l%nSystem is listed as %T%n
          Operated by %s%nRegion %R, Hub %h%nPhone %P
          , Cost %c%nFlags %f%nPassword %w%n"
     is used.

 NODELIST --- @{b}Directory@{ub} where the nodelist files are kept. Defaults to
     "NodeList:". Note the traplist.library is used, not the new glist.library!

 STRIPDASHES --- Remove dashes from phonenumber before searching. Only used
     if STYPE=phone is also used.
@endnode
@remark &&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&
@node HIST "Version History"

26.11.95 
         - Combined the source and distributions of FindPhone, FindPlace,
           FindSysop and FindSystem.
         - Added STOP option
         - Added LFORMAT option
         - Fixed a memory leak
         - Added VERBATIM option to all commands  

13.12.95
         - Fixed a small memory leak, ReadArgs was not being freed. 

16.12.95 : 1.67
         - Integrated FindSystem, FindSysop, FindPlace and FindPhone into
           one program (FindXXX). The STYPE option can now be used to specify
           the type of search required.
@endnode
